headlines.description: — Kevin Durant came back and Joel Embiid waved him off the floor.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid scores 34, 76ers beat Nets 110-102 in Durant's return

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo scored 33 points, Jrue Holiday added 25 points and Khris Middleton had 22 as the Milwaukee Bucks extended their winning streak to five games with a 136-118 victory over the Orlando Magic on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bucks complete sweep of Magic 136-118, push win streak to 5

headlines.description: — Bradley Beal had 29 points and 10 assists in his first game back from the NBA’s health and safety protocols as the Washington Wizards beat the Cleveland Cavaliers 110-93 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Beal scores 29 in return, Wizards beat Cavaliers 110-93

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Denver Nuggets
